Installation package description

  README         - This file
  LICENSE        - License
  ChangeLog      - History of enhancement

Contents of the directory tree is below.

  ./source       - Sources of UCMQ
  ./client       - Client of UCMQ(Development of language: c)
  ./conf         - The configuration file of UCMQ 
  ./test         - Test tool

Please read the following documents, Then will describes how to install UCMQ.

1. The necessary Installation environment is ready to
  operating system - Linux/*nix (i686/x86_64/amd64)
  gcc version      - >= 4.1.2
  libevent version - >= 2.0.10

2. Building and installation 
  ./genall.sh
  ./configure --with-libevent=LIBEVENT_DIR --prefix=PREFIX_DIR
  make && make install

3. Get usage
  ./ucmq -h       - help
  ./ucmq -v       - display version info

4. start UCMQ
  ./ucmq  -c ../conf/ucmq.ini [ -d ]

5. test
  ./curl "http://ip:port/?name=test&opt=put&data=hello&ver2"

6. Monitoring status, Please use the browser to access:
  http://ip:port/stat 

UCMQ was written by ShaneYuan.  You can contact the author
by e-mail to `osucmq@ucweb.com'.

Thanks.

